comments.text:
Hi Jetstar. I really need your help getting home. I was originally meant to fly home on the 07/11/15 JQ38 to Sydney but it was cancelled. We have been stuck in Bali since then. 
We were lucky to be scheduled on a 7.05 am flight to Darwin with a layover then onto Sydney on the 13/11/15 however this flight was cancelled. We were informed by your Jetstar staff at Denpasar airport that we would be scheduled on the following day due to the dire situation we are in at the moment (no accommodation or money) they offered us meal vouchers for use in the airport only and assure us we would be on the following day flight home. 
Saturday and Sunday flights then went out and we were not booked on them! 
I called your 24 hour assistance line this morning and explained again our situation and they said they would send us out itinerary for tomorrow.

I am yet to receive itinerary for our booking and have called again tonight to be told we are on a priority list. I had the your rep Lanie escalate the call to a team leader because as from tomorrow we will have no accommodation, no money to eat, we are both at a high risk that we are going to lose our jobs, I have been having anxiety attacks, I need new contact lenses filled and do not have money to fill it or my prescription with me as I need to replace my monthly lenses, our insurance is not letting us make a interim claim to get some money back and is saying we cannot make a claim until we claim the whole amount to which will take 10 business days to refund, I need to pay rent and at the moment if I don't return to work will be homeless upon my return to Australia. 
I am sorry to go on and on but that is the situation and we need to be put on a Monday flight. 
I would appreciate a quick response as I do not know what else to do.
